1
00:00:05,172 --> 00:00:08,039
[instrumental music]

2
00:00:14,681 --> 00:00:15,796
whoosh

3
00:00:20,854 --> 00:00:21,969
whoosh

4
00:00:29,321 --> 00:00:30,436
whoosh

5
00:00:32,574 --> 00:00:33,689
splash

6
00:00:38,872 --> 00:00:41,204
A little sharp on the turn, don't you think?

7
00:00:41,416 --> 00:00:43,407
Sorry if I scared you.

8
00:01:08,110 --> 00:01:09,066
What did you get him?

9
00:01:09,278 --> 00:01:10,689
I'm not saying anything.

10
00:01:10,904 --> 00:01:13,236
He'll hear and spoil the surprise.

11
00:01:13,448 --> 00:01:15,940
He can hear that, too.

12
00:01:16,159 --> 00:01:17,945
How about you?

13
00:01:18,161 --> 00:01:19,572
He's not the easiest person in the world

14
00:01:19,788 --> 00:01:21,529
to buy birthday presents for.

15
00:01:23,041 --> 00:01:25,499
Bruce, you didn't get him a gift certificate?

16
00:01:25,711 --> 00:01:27,543
No.

17
00:01:27,754 --> 00:01:28,835
Cash.

18
00:01:31,466 --> 00:01:33,833
I mean, what do you buy for the man who has everything..

19
00:01:45,981 --> 00:01:48,222
[theme music]

20
00:02:54,591 --> 00:02:56,377
Looks like some kind of plant.

21
00:02:56,593 --> 00:02:57,833
Seems to be to be growing through his costume

22
00:02:58,053 --> 00:03:00,670
and into his body.

23
00:03:00,889 --> 00:03:02,425
Is he breathing?

24
00:03:02,641 --> 00:03:04,097
Barely.

25
00:03:04,309 --> 00:03:05,845
Someone must have breached the fortress.

26
00:03:06,061 --> 00:03:08,678
Agreed. Have a look around.

27
00:03:11,900 --> 00:03:14,141
Pupils aren't contracting even slightly.

28
00:03:14,361 --> 00:03:17,069
He must be cut off from all sensation.

29
00:03:17,280 --> 00:03:19,612
Kent, where are you?

30
00:03:23,495 --> 00:03:25,327
[beeping]

31
00:03:25,539 --> 00:03:27,871
(Brainiac) 'This is your wake-up alarm.'

32
00:03:34,423 --> 00:03:37,336
Good morning, Kal-El, and happy birthday.

33
00:03:37,551 --> 00:03:38,586
[yawning]

34
00:03:38,802 --> 00:03:40,042
Thanks, Brainiac.

35
00:03:40,262 --> 00:03:41,343
Windows, please.

36
00:03:56,820 --> 00:03:58,982
[yawning]

37
00:03:59,197 --> 00:04:02,781
Please don't tell me it's morning already.

38
00:04:02,993 --> 00:04:04,108
[groaning]

39
00:04:04,327 --> 00:04:06,694
That's what you get for partying all night.

40
00:04:06,913 --> 00:04:08,278
I was working.

41
00:04:08,498 --> 00:04:10,580
Come on, honey. You call that work?

42
00:04:10,792 --> 00:04:14,205
Covering the opening of the Argo City Museum of Modern Art?

43
00:04:14,421 --> 00:04:18,085
Hobnobbing with all the movers and shakers?

44
00:04:18,300 --> 00:04:21,088
Mmm, a bunch of bores.

45
00:04:21,303 --> 00:04:22,964
You could have come, you know.

46
00:04:23,180 --> 00:04:24,011
Next time.

47
00:04:24,222 --> 00:04:25,678
Oh, please.

48
00:04:25,891 --> 00:04:27,131
I couldn't get you off this farm

49
00:04:27,350 --> 00:04:29,091
if I exploded a quantum bomb under your--

50
00:04:29,311 --> 00:04:31,473
[rumbling]

51
00:04:34,608 --> 00:04:37,600
Did you...unh!

52
00:04:37,819 --> 00:04:40,151
Come here, handsome.

53
00:04:42,824 --> 00:04:44,189
(Brainiac) 'A gentle reminder.'

54
00:04:44,409 --> 00:04:45,865
Kal-El and Van-El are expected

55
00:04:46,077 --> 00:04:48,193
at Jor-El's laboratory in precisely 2 hours

56
00:04:48,413 --> 00:04:51,781
and 12 minutes, and the Vac-40 is overdue for inspection.

57
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:53,991
Shut up!

58
00:04:55,212 --> 00:04:56,668
Hmm.

59
00:04:59,424 --> 00:05:02,462
(Batman) 'So it was a gift.'

60
00:05:02,677 --> 00:05:04,509
Teleported here from some alien culture

61
00:05:04,721 --> 00:05:06,712
some grateful world.

62
00:05:06,932 --> 00:05:09,139
Or someone wanting you to think they were grateful.

63
00:05:10,977 --> 00:05:12,718
(Mongul) 'How remarkable.'

64
00:05:12,938 --> 00:05:16,556
'You animals really are almost intelligent, aren't you?'

65
00:05:16,775 --> 00:05:19,107
That's exactly what happened.

66
00:05:22,781 --> 00:05:24,271
Mongul.

67
00:05:24,491 --> 00:05:27,153
You recognize me. I'm flattered.

68
00:05:27,369 --> 00:05:31,738
I suppose Superman told you all about our previous encounter.

69
00:05:31,957 --> 00:05:34,164
You mean how he humiliated you?

70
00:05:34,376 --> 00:05:37,368
A...jaundiced account.

71
00:05:39,506 --> 00:05:42,919
What inferior specimens he surrounds himself with.

72
00:05:43,134 --> 00:05:46,593
I took her down before she even knew I was there

73
00:05:46,805 --> 00:05:49,718
and I'll take this planet just as easily.

74
00:05:51,560 --> 00:05:52,675
Hyah!

75
00:05:54,271 --> 00:05:56,353
Maybe not as easily as you think.

76
00:05:56,565 --> 00:05:58,272
Grr.

77
00:05:58,483 --> 00:06:02,021
We inferior specimens call it "playing possum".

78
00:06:04,114 --> 00:06:06,481
- No. - No?

79
00:06:06,700 --> 00:06:10,534
Clearly the males on this world are the smart ones.

80
00:06:10,745 --> 00:06:15,034
He wants to know about the plant.

81
00:06:15,250 --> 00:06:17,662
The Black Mercy is a telepathic species.

82
00:06:17,878 --> 00:06:20,745
It reads the heart's desire and feeds the individual

83
00:06:20,964 --> 00:06:23,251
a totally convincing simulation of it.

84
00:06:24,217 --> 00:06:25,924
So he's dreaming?

85
00:06:26,136 --> 00:06:28,468
Oh, far deeper than any dream.

86
00:06:30,015 --> 00:06:32,256
I wonder where he thinks he is.

87
00:06:32,475 --> 00:06:34,887
(Mongul) Sitting on a throne ruling the universe

88
00:06:35,103 --> 00:06:37,891
all you human garbage fawning at his feet?

89
00:06:38,106 --> 00:06:39,596
More honest, don't you think

90
00:06:39,816 --> 00:06:42,808
than this pretense of being a selfless hero?

91
00:06:43,028 --> 00:06:44,109
Hyah!

92
00:06:50,452 --> 00:06:52,193
You don't understand.

93
00:06:52,412 --> 00:06:55,404
He was the only obstacle in my way.

94
00:06:55,624 --> 00:06:58,582
The rest of you are already dead.

95
00:07:01,421 --> 00:07:02,536
sizzle

96
00:07:05,342 --> 00:07:08,505
Van! Van, your breakfast is getting cold.

97
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:09,801
<i>(Van) 'I'm coming.'</i>

98
00:07:10,013 --> 00:07:11,094
Ooh!

99
00:07:12,682 --> 00:07:15,140
Looks like the dog left you a present.

100
00:07:15,352 --> 00:07:17,138
Brainiac?

101
00:07:17,395 --> 00:07:19,102
Could you clean up that..

102
00:07:22,025 --> 00:07:23,732
No, Brainiac.

103
00:07:23,944 --> 00:07:26,356
Van was supposed to walk the dog.

104
00:07:28,198 --> 00:07:29,814
It's his job to clean it up.

105
00:07:30,033 --> 00:07:31,774
Van-El, I want you down here right--

106
00:07:31,993 --> 00:07:34,200
(Van) 'I'm here, I'm here!'

107
00:07:35,497 --> 00:07:37,909
[dog whimpers]

108
00:07:38,124 --> 00:07:39,205
It's okay, Krypto.

109
00:07:39,417 --> 00:07:41,749
How many times do I have to tell you, Van?

110
00:07:41,962 --> 00:07:43,578
When you asked for a dog, you--

111
00:07:43,797 --> 00:07:47,665
Promised to take care of it. I know. Sorry, dad.

112
00:07:51,680 --> 00:07:53,921
Sorry's not always enough. We have to--

113
00:07:54,140 --> 00:07:55,756
Live up to our responsibilities.

114
00:07:55,976 --> 00:07:57,717
I know, I know!

115
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:02,346
whirr

116
00:08:02,565 --> 00:08:04,602
This mean I can't come to the party?

117
00:08:04,818 --> 00:08:05,933
Oops.

118
00:08:06,152 --> 00:08:08,359
What party is that?

119
00:08:08,571 --> 00:08:11,404
Uh, the, uh..

120
00:08:11,616 --> 00:08:13,027
You're confused, Van.

121
00:08:13,243 --> 00:08:15,154
Little Zod's party isn't till next--

122
00:08:15,370 --> 00:08:18,488
I told you I didn't want a surprise party.

123
00:08:18,707 --> 00:08:20,414
And you're not getting one.

124
00:08:20,625 --> 00:08:21,706
Eat your breakfast, Van.

125
00:08:21,918 --> 00:08:22,749
You and dad don't want to be late

126
00:08:22,961 --> 00:08:24,417
visiting grandpa Jor-El.

127
00:08:24,629 --> 00:08:26,495
(Brainiac) Indeed. Traffic on the Kandor skyway

128
00:08:26,715 --> 00:08:28,001
is backed up to the gold volcano.

129
00:08:28,216 --> 00:08:30,423
Kandor. I forgot!

130
00:08:32,679 --> 00:08:34,886
I don't want a surprise party.

131
00:08:35,098 --> 00:08:37,430
It's just a small one.

132
00:08:49,904 --> 00:08:52,145
[dramatic music]

133
00:08:54,826 --> 00:08:55,941
Huh!

134
00:08:56,161 --> 00:08:58,493
[grunting]

135
00:09:07,589 --> 00:09:09,171
Unh'!

136
00:09:09,382 --> 00:09:10,247
Ohh!

137
00:09:14,262 --> 00:09:16,299
(Mongul) 'How nice of you to volunteer..'

138
00:09:18,183 --> 00:09:20,925
...to be the first of your race to die.

139
00:09:21,144 --> 00:09:22,509
Rrarr!

140
00:09:22,729 --> 00:09:25,721
Unh! Ohh! Unh!

141
00:09:27,650 --> 00:09:28,890
[groaning]

142
00:09:34,699 --> 00:09:37,361
zzzt

143
00:09:47,837 --> 00:09:48,952
(Wonder Woman) 'Unh!'

144
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:53,256
He'll kill her, Clark.

145
00:09:53,468 --> 00:09:54,708
And then he'll kill us all.

146
00:09:54,928 --> 00:09:56,919
Shake it off. Come back to us.

147
00:09:58,431 --> 00:09:59,546
(Batman) 'Please.'

148
00:10:08,191 --> 00:10:09,272
Aah!

149
00:10:17,742 --> 00:10:20,700
Oh, dear. Is that a Neural Impactor?

150
00:10:20,912 --> 00:10:23,654
I didn't know they were still making those.

151
00:10:25,875 --> 00:10:29,084
I'd advise you to try the plasma disruptor.

152
00:10:29,295 --> 00:10:31,787
It's more of a woman's weapon.

153
00:10:32,507 --> 00:10:33,872
Go, to..

154
00:10:34,092 --> 00:10:35,173
zap

155
00:10:46,813 --> 00:10:48,178
Nothing's working!

156
00:10:48,398 --> 00:10:50,685
boom

157
00:10:50,900 --> 00:10:52,356
She's in the hall of weapons.

158
00:10:52,569 --> 00:10:55,152
That will buy her time, but not enough.

159
00:10:55,363 --> 00:10:57,445
She's fighting for her life, Clark.

160
00:10:57,657 --> 00:10:59,147
(Batman) You've got to fight, too.

161
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:10,542
I can't believe you left all this

162
00:11:10,753 --> 00:11:12,744
to live on a farm.

163
00:11:12,964 --> 00:11:14,546
It's a nice place to visit, but..

164
00:11:14,757 --> 00:11:15,963
[rumbling]

165
00:11:16,176 --> 00:11:17,382
Van, did you--

166
00:11:17,594 --> 00:11:18,675
Grandpa!

167
00:11:22,891 --> 00:11:24,097
Brainiac?

168
00:11:24,309 --> 00:11:26,346
A minor and completely harmless tremor.

169
00:11:26,561 --> 00:11:29,178
Predicted several weeks ago by the Seismic Institute.

170
00:11:33,943 --> 00:11:35,058
zzzt

171
00:11:46,372 --> 00:11:47,737
[growling]

172
00:11:47,957 --> 00:11:50,449
First, I'll kill you and the Bat

173
00:11:50,668 --> 00:11:52,955
and then I'll take this planet.

174
00:11:53,171 --> 00:11:55,162
You won't win.

175
00:11:55,381 --> 00:11:57,713
Of course I will.

176
00:11:57,926 --> 00:11:59,792
[grunts]

177
00:12:02,889 --> 00:12:03,879
(Wonder Woman) 'Aah!'

178
00:12:06,351 --> 00:12:07,933
[squeaking]

179
00:12:09,979 --> 00:12:12,186
What's this one, grandpa?

180
00:12:12,398 --> 00:12:14,605
And this?

181
00:12:14,817 --> 00:12:16,603
Whoa! Where'd you get--

182
00:12:16,819 --> 00:12:18,526
One minute, Van.

183
00:12:18,738 --> 00:12:20,024
Something's bothering you.

184
00:12:23,243 --> 00:12:24,825
Here..

185
00:12:25,036 --> 00:12:27,368
...and here and here.

186
00:12:27,580 --> 00:12:30,493
A series of mild tremors. Not unusual.

187
00:12:30,708 --> 00:12:32,995
- I don't see what-- - Something's wrong, dad.

188
00:12:33,211 --> 00:12:35,373
Something's going to happen. I can feel it in--

189
00:12:35,588 --> 00:12:37,170
Oh. So you're a scientist now?

190
00:12:37,382 --> 00:12:38,247
Dad.

191
00:12:38,466 --> 00:12:39,422
Do I have to remind you about

192
00:12:39,634 --> 00:12:40,999
a certain prediction of my own?

193
00:12:41,219 --> 00:12:42,755
Made, I'm embarrassed to say

194
00:12:42,971 --> 00:12:44,757
when you were only a few days old?

195
00:12:44,973 --> 00:12:46,008
I announced to the world that

196
00:12:46,224 --> 00:12:47,931
Krypton was going to explode

197
00:12:48,142 --> 00:12:50,884
and it took me years to salvage my reputation.

198
00:12:51,104 --> 00:12:53,436
But maybe you were right, maybe..

199
00:12:57,694 --> 00:12:59,731
Maybe I've just been working too hard.

200
00:13:01,197 --> 00:13:02,858
The past is dead.

201
00:13:03,074 --> 00:13:05,190
Focus on the future.

202
00:13:05,410 --> 00:13:07,026
Can we go up to the roof, grandpa?

203
00:13:07,245 --> 00:13:09,327
Somebody wants to see the macroscope.

204
00:13:09,539 --> 00:13:11,280
Go on up with your father, Van.

205
00:13:11,499 --> 00:13:13,866
I'll be along in a few minutes.

206
00:13:14,794 --> 00:13:15,704
Let's go.

207
00:13:27,098 --> 00:13:28,384
It's not right.

208
00:13:34,772 --> 00:13:37,184
Yes. That's it.

209
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:39,016
Fight it, Clark.

210
00:13:39,235 --> 00:13:40,191
Fight it.

211
00:13:43,906 --> 00:13:45,613
(Batman) Fight it.

212
00:13:45,825 --> 00:13:46,781
Dad?

213
00:13:46,993 --> 00:13:47,903
[rumbling]

214
00:13:48,119 --> 00:13:49,484
.(Van)

215
00:13:49,704 --> 00:13:51,866
You've got to look at thi..

216
00:13:53,833 --> 00:13:56,165
What's...what's the matter?

217
00:13:57,003 --> 00:13:58,960
Why are you..

218
00:13:59,172 --> 00:14:01,630
Van, when you were born

219
00:14:01,841 --> 00:14:04,708
it was the happiest day of my life.

220
00:14:04,927 --> 00:14:07,840
When I first saw your beautiful little face

221
00:14:08,056 --> 00:14:11,048
your tiny fingers squeezed my hand so tight.

222
00:14:12,352 --> 00:14:14,684
Like you never wanted to let go.

223
00:14:14,896 --> 00:14:18,014
I've watched every step, every struggle.

224
00:14:18,232 --> 00:14:20,724
I've...but Van..

225
00:14:20,943 --> 00:14:22,775
Rao, help me.

226
00:14:22,987 --> 00:14:25,354
But I don't think you're real.

227
00:14:25,573 --> 00:14:28,110
I don't think any of this is-is real.

228
00:14:28,326 --> 00:14:29,657
Don't say that, daddy.

229
00:14:29,869 --> 00:14:31,906
Please. You're scaring me.

230
00:14:32,121 --> 00:14:35,364
No, no. I don't want to scare you, Van.

231
00:14:35,583 --> 00:14:38,666
You are everything I ever wanted in a son.

232
00:14:38,878 --> 00:14:40,164
This..

233
00:14:40,380 --> 00:14:43,338
This is everything I ever wanted in a life.

234
00:14:45,635 --> 00:14:47,967
But I've got responsibilities, Van.

235
00:14:48,179 --> 00:14:50,045
And...I..

236
00:14:50,264 --> 00:14:51,470
...have to go now.

237
00:14:55,186 --> 00:14:57,268
[rumbling]

238
00:15:00,483 --> 00:15:02,724
[explosion]

239
00:15:12,912 --> 00:15:14,027
Daddy.

240
00:15:17,083 --> 00:15:18,744
I promise you.

241
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:21,292
I'll never forget.

242
00:15:23,589 --> 00:15:25,956
[explosion]

243
00:15:28,511 --> 00:15:29,626
Yes!

244
00:15:30,721 --> 00:15:32,337
Unh'!

245
00:15:35,309 --> 00:15:37,175
(child Bruce) Beware my terrible sword.

246
00:15:43,234 --> 00:15:44,269
Ha ha!

247
00:15:44,485 --> 00:15:46,817
Let all evildoers beware my..

248
00:15:55,830 --> 00:15:57,571
We'll start with the pretty pearls

249
00:15:57,790 --> 00:15:59,406
around the lady's neck.

250
00:16:02,003 --> 00:16:03,334
Now.

251
00:16:12,763 --> 00:16:13,753
Aah!

252
00:16:13,973 --> 00:16:15,054
Yes!

253
00:16:15,766 --> 00:16:16,881
Aah!

254
00:16:23,274 --> 00:16:25,641
boom boom

255
00:16:37,121 --> 00:16:39,408
[grunts]

256
00:16:47,340 --> 00:16:48,455
whoosh

257
00:16:50,927 --> 00:16:52,338
clang

258
00:16:52,553 --> 00:16:53,634
[crashing]

259
00:16:56,682 --> 00:16:57,797
thud

260
00:17:04,607 --> 00:17:07,690
Do you have any idea what you did to me?

261
00:17:11,280 --> 00:17:13,396
Aah!

262
00:17:21,666 --> 00:17:23,077
Unh'!

263
00:17:24,961 --> 00:17:26,918
I fashioned a prison that you couldn't leave

264
00:17:27,129 --> 00:17:29,461
without sacrificing your heart's desire.

265
00:17:29,674 --> 00:17:31,381
crackle

266
00:17:31,592 --> 00:17:34,960
(Mongul) It must have been like tearing off your own arm.

267
00:17:41,435 --> 00:17:43,051
[grunts]

268
00:17:53,364 --> 00:17:55,275
Aah!

269
00:17:56,242 --> 00:17:58,358
Unh'!

270
00:18:07,753 --> 00:18:10,165
Bruce.

271
00:18:21,851 --> 00:18:24,263
Happy birthday, Kryptonian.

272
00:18:24,478 --> 00:18:26,890
I give you oblivion.

273
00:18:27,857 --> 00:18:28,972
Burn.

274
00:18:30,651 --> 00:18:31,766
Aah!

275
00:18:42,121 --> 00:18:43,236
[panting]

276
00:18:50,755 --> 00:18:53,122
Hera, no!

277
00:19:02,892 --> 00:19:04,724
Bruce!

278
00:19:04,935 --> 00:19:07,973
Get him, dad, get him!

279
00:19:10,608 --> 00:19:12,975
(Wonder Woman) Bruce!

280
00:19:22,244 --> 00:19:23,154
Aah!

281
00:19:34,799 --> 00:19:37,382
You should have stayed in whatever happy fantasy

